To run: node app.js

To debug: node debug app.js
To see the avalible options for debug mode, use: help
If you want to debug an explicit line, use: setBreakpoint(n), here set the number line.

********** Create a NPM project
npm init

To add modules use:

npm install <module> -save, example: npm install express -save 

To unistall a module use:

npm uninstall <module>

When you use: -save, add the module at the package.json

If you have a package.json with all dependencies that you require use:

npm install

If you need a module that update your files after every change that you do, install:

npm install nomode -g 

The letter -g, means that the module will be installed the global way

To use nodemon use: nodemon yourapp.js

